verbose_text: The results revealed that Evo dose-dependently reduced the protein and mRNA expression levels of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, interleukin (IL) -6 and IL-1beta, and inhibited the levels of phosphorylated (p-) inhibitor of NF-kappaBalpha, p-extracellular signal regulated kinase, p-c-Jun N-terminal kinase and p-p38, and decreased the nuclear trans-location of NF-kappaB / p65 in BEAS-2B cells infected with MSSA.
evidence: Evo dose-dependently reduced the protein and mRNA expression levels of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, interleukin (IL)-6 and IL-1beta
